DURBAN - The SA National Defence Force has released the names of three sailors who died at a naval base in Durban on Friday.Leading Seaman Amrithlall Ramdin, Able Seaman Francois Mundell and Seaman Henro Ter Borg have been praised for the rescue attempt that ultimately led to their deaths.They were overcome by fumes when they went to the aid of three Public Works contractors who had been overwhelmed by gas in a sewage pit. They were unable to save the three and succumbed to the gas themselves. A navy board of inquiry has been set up and police are also investigating. Minister of Defence Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula has sent condolences to the families of the six who died.eNCA